article.title: Molecular Gas Dominated 50 kpc Ram Pressure Stripped Tail of the Coma Galaxy D100

multiple_choice_question.text: Which panel of Figure 1 shows the presence of dust extinction filaments in D100?
At what approximate distance from the galaxy is the strongest CO emission in the tail of D100 observed?
What trend is observed in the CO(2-1)/(1-0) integrated intensity line ratios along the tail of D100?
choices: The ratio decreases with increasing distance from the galaxy.
The ratio remains constant along the tail.
The ratio increases with increasing distance from the galaxy.

multiple_choice_question.text: What is the approximate velocity offset between the CO emission and the mean Ha velocities in the D100 tail?
What does the parameter D represent in Formula 1?
choices: Distance to the galaxy in parsecs
Diameter of the telescope in meters
Distance to the galaxy in megaparsecs
Velocity integrated line flux in Jy km/s
